And it's an interesting industry to be in at the moment because, as you all know, there's a huge amount of upheaval going on in media. And most of you probably know this from the business angle, which is that the business model is pretty screwed. And as my grandfather would say, the profits have all been gobbled up by Google. So M. It's a really interesting time to be a journalist. But the upheaval that I'm interested in is not in the output side. It's on the input side. It's concerned with how we get information and how we gather. The news on that's changed because we've had a huge shift in the balance of power from the news organizations to the audience on the audience for such a long time was in a position where they didn't have any way of affecting news or making any change. They couldn't really connect, and that's that's changed irrevocably. My first connection with the news media WAAS In 1984 the BBC had a one day strike. I wasn't happy. I was angry.
